The Disneyland in Polokwane event has left parents fuming after it failed to live up to standards. JOHANNESBURG - Parents and kids in Polokwane had a nightmare on Saturday. They were attending the Disneyland in Polokwane event. But it failed to live up to standards, resulting in conflict as parents demanded a refund. READ: Disney again posts $7bn in earnings Meanwhile, Disney Africa has stressed that this was not their event and say they are investigating. The Flying Fish logo can be seen on the flyer, but the alcohol brand has already distanced itself from the event. It is investigating the use of its brand logo as it did not sponsor the event. Attempts to get hold of the organisers and the lodge have proved fruitless.